  "prompt": "What are the best documentary channels on youtube?",
  "response": "YouTube hosts a variety of excellent documentary channels that cater to diverse interests. Here are some of the best documentary channels available on the platform:\n\n### True Story & Crime Documentaries\n1. **Real Stories** - Offers a wide range of documentaries on social issues, crime, history, and more.\n2. **Crime Zone** - Focuses on true crime stories and investigative documentaries.\n3. **JCS - Criminal Psychology** - Analyzes police interrogations and criminal behavior with a psychological perspective.\n\n### Nature & Science Documentaries\n1. **BBC Earth** - Known for high-quality nature and wildlife documentaries.\n2. **National Geographic** - Covers a broad spectrum of topics including nature, science, and exploration.\n3. **Kurzgesagt \u2013 In a Nutshell** - Provides animated documentaries on science, technology, and philosophy.\n\n### History & Culture Documentaries\n1. **Timeline** - Offers historical documentaries on a wide range of topics and periods.\n2. **The Great War** - Focuses on World War I with in-depth episodes and specials.\n3. **PBS Eons** - Explores the history of life on Earth through paleontology and evolutionary biology.\n\n### Independent & Niche Documentaries\n1. **VICE** - Covers a variety of topics including current events, culture, and global issues.\n2. **DW Documentary** - Features high-quality documentaries on global issues, history, and culture.\n3. **Channel 4 Documentaries** - Offers a diverse range of documentaries on social issues, current affairs, and more.\n\n### Educational Documentaries\n1. **TED-Ed** - Provides educational videos and documentaries on a wide range of topics.\n2. **CrashCourse** - Offers concise educational series on various subjects including history, science, and literature.\n3. **Khan Academy** - While primarily an educational platform, it includes documentary-style videos on various academic subjects.\n\n### Alternative & In-Depth Documentaries\n1. **AlternateHistoryHub** - Explores speculative histories and what-if scenarios.\n2. **Extra Credits** - Offers documentaries on topics like history, game design, and mythology.\n3. **Bright Sun Films** - Focuses on abandoned places, bankrupt companies, and other fascinating topics.\n\nThese channels provide a wealth of content across different genres and interests, making them excellent resources for documentary enthusiasts.",
